In general, starch viscosity increased exponentially with concentration, whereas XG viscosity increased in a more linear manner. Therefore, to make CLS a viable industrial alternative to XG, it is necessary to adjust its viscosity to match that of XG at varying concentrations. Referring to previous study (Park and Kim, 2023), the curve estimation technique was applied to determine the relationship between the apparent viscosity of CLS and XG at a shear rate of 50 s⁻1, resulting in the following equation:2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
