				\begin{document}$$ {\text{Y}} = \, 0.573 \, \times \, \ln \, \left( {\text{X}} \right) \, + \, 1.627 $$\end{document}Y=0.573×lnX+1.627where X is the XG concentration and Y is the CLS concentration. However, the apparent viscosity in steady-state flow tests depends on the shear rate, as both CLS and XG are non-Newtonian materials. Therefore, the above formula needs to include terms for the shear rate. Consequently, a relational formula that incorporates the viscosities of both CLS and XG, as well as the shear rate, was derived as follows:3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
